explain cloud deployment models as per the nist guidelines
<extra_id_1>Assistant
The cloud deployment models identified by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) include:


 -  Public cloud, in which cloud services are provided by a service provider and made available to the general public over the internet;


 -  Private cloud, in which cloud services are provided by an organization for internal use by employees, partners, or customers;


 -  Community cloud, in which cloud services are provided by an organization for use by a community of interest, such as government agencies or academic institutions;


 -  Hybrid cloud, in which cloud services are provided by an organization using a combination of public and private cloud infrastructure.
